# 🏢 Executor Framework

The Executor Framework manages thread pools efficiently.

```java id="7djlwm"
import java.util.concurrent.*;

ExecutorService service =
Executors.newFixedThreadPool(3);

service.execute(() -> {
    System.out.println("Task Executed");
});

service.shutdown();
```

